# ============================================================
# Non-secret defaults committed to git.
#
# Real secrets (NEXTAUTH_SECRET, DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD, etc.) and the
# real DATABASE_URL belong in `.env.local` for local development, and in
# the hosting provider's environment settings for production (Vercel →
# Project → Settings → Environment Variables). Values in `.env.local`
# and Vercel env vars override what is set here.
#
# On Vercel: provisioning Vercel Postgres auto-populates DATABASE_URL
# in the project env — nothing else needed for the DB connection.
#
# See .env.example for the full list of variables the app expects.
# ============================================================

# Placeholder so `prisma generate` can resolve the schema during CI /
# build even before the real connection string is set. Real value must
# be provided via .env.local (local) or Vercel env vars (production).
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://placeholder:placeholder@localhost:5432/placeholder?schema=public"
